The article is a statement by the President on the House passing the Don't Ask, Don't Tell Repeal Act of 2010. The President applauds the bipartisan support for the legislation and highlights that the Secretary of Defense and the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff support the repeal. The President emphasizes that the repeal process will allow for a smooth transition while maintaining order and discipline in the military. The article also mentions that the Service Chiefs have stated they will implement the transition effectively and efficiently. The President thanks Speaker Nancy Pelosi, Majority Leader Steny Hoyer, and Congressman Patrick Murphy for their leadership on this issue. The President believes that repealing this law is the right thing to do and will provide clarity and certainty for the military. He emphasizes the importance of treating Americans who are willing to risk their lives for their country fairly and equally.